---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About CMS"
  description="Learn about Colorado Muslim Society's mission and history in Denver."
  noIndex
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <section class="section about-intro">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>About Colorado Muslim Society</h1>
        <p class="muted">Serving the Muslim community of Denver and surrounding areas since 1964.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container two-col about-top-grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h2>Core Values</h2>
          <p>Colorado Muslim Society honors the following core values:</p>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>Adhere to Islamic principles as enshrined in the Quran and Sunnah</li>
            <li>Respectful and inclusive of the diversity of community</li>
            <li>Transparency of operations</li>
            <li>Emphasis on community participation</li>
            <li>Commitment to growth and development</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="card about-vm">
          <h2>Vision</h2>
          <p>To please Allah (The Creator) by serving Islam and Muslims.</p>
          <h2>Mission</h2>
          <p>
            To serve the best interests of Islam and Muslims in Colorado by providing religious, educational,
            and cultural programs for men, women, and youth in our community. Introduce Islam according to the
            Quran and the Sunnah through dialogues and dawah activities.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <article class="card about-history-card">
          <h2>CMS History</h2>
          <p>
            In 1964, the Colorado Muslim Society (CMS) was incorporated and registered with the State of
            Colorado as a religious, non-profit, non-political, cultural, social, educational, and
            humanitarian organization.
          </p>

          <h2 class="about-inline-heading">The First Masjid in Colorado</h2>
          <p>
            In 1974, a building was purchased and it became the first masjid in Colorado at 1401 Ash Street,
            Denver.
          </p>

          <h2 class="about-inline-heading">First Phase Construction</h2>
          <p>
            In 1978, approximately a four-acre lot at 2071 South Parker Road, Denver, CO 80231 was purchased.
            This is where CMS is located today.
          </p>
          <p>
            In November 1983, the first phase of construction was completed under Project Manager Br. Abdul
            Hakim Minhas, P.E.
          </p>
          <p>The following areas were built:</p>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>The mosque (main prayer hall for men and women)</li>
            <li>Four classrooms for the weekend Islamic school</li>
            <li>Kitchen</li>
            <li>Separate wudu/ablution areas and bathrooms for women and men</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="about-inline-heading">Second Phase Construction</h2>
          <p>
            The second phase was completed in 2004 under the supervision of Br. Abdul Hakim Minhas, P.E. and
            Br. Talibudin Syed, P.E.
          </p>
          <p>The following areas were added:</p>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>Multi-purpose room</li>
            <li>Additional classrooms</li>
            <li>Office/management area</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
